# pytest cache directory #

This directory contains data from the pytest's cache plugin,
which provides the `--lf` and `--ff` options, as well as the `cache` fixture.

**Do not** commit this to version control.

See [the docs](https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/cache.html) for more information.


--------------------
[ASSISTANT/LLM]:
 The project is related to a pytest cache plugin, which is designed to enhance the functionality of the pytest testing framework by providing two key features: `--lf` (last failed) and `--ff` (first failed) options. These options allow users to rerun only the tests that have failed in previous runs or those that are expected to fail first, respectively. Additionally, it includes a cache fixture that enables persistent caching of test data between test sessions. It is important to note that this plugin should not be committed to version control as it contains transient data specific to individual testing environments. For more detailed information, refer to the official pytest documentation on caching capabilities.
