class RsRegister:
    """
    The `RsRegister` class is designed to manage and reset various text formatting styles, including bold, italic, underline, and more. It provides instances that can be used to reset single effects such as foregrounds and backgrounds.

    Parameters:
        - None (the function does not accept any parameters)

    Returns:
        An instance of the `RsRegister` class which contains properties for controlling text formatting including bold, italic, underline, and more.

    Example Usage:
        ```python
        rs = RsRegister()
        
        print(f"{rs.italic}Italic Text{rs.italic}")  # Prints italicized text using the reset register
        print(f"{rs.underl}Underlined Text{rs.underl}")  # Prints underlined text using the reset register
        print(f"{fg.red}{rs.italic}Red Italic Text{rs.all}")  # Prints red italicized text with all effects reset
