```python
class RgbBg:
    """
    Define RGB Background.
    
    This class initializes an object representing a color in the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) format for use as a background color in a terminal or console application. The colors are specified using integers between 0 and 255, which correspond to the intensity of each color component.
    
    More info about 24-bit terminal colors: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#24-bit
    
    :param r: Red component of the RGB color (integer between 0 and 255).
    :param g: Green component of the RGB color (integer between 0 and 255).
    :param b: Blue component of the RGB color (integer between 0 and 255).
    
    Example:
        To create a background color with red intensity 128, green intensity 64, and blue intensity 32, you would use:
        
        rgb_bg = RgbBg(128, 64, 32)
        
        This will set the RGB values to (128, 64, 32), which can be used in terminal settings or any application that supports custom background colors.
    """
    def __init__(self, r: int, g: int, b: int):
        if not (0 <= r <= 255) or not (0 <= g <= 255) or not (0 <= b <= 255):
            raise ValueError("RGB values must be between 0 and 255")
        self.r = r
        self.g = g
        self.b = b
```

